casebody.data:
McBRIDE, Appellant, v. VENABLE et al., Respondents. (Common Pleas of New York City and County, General Term. March 8, 1894.) Appeal from special term. Action by Robert 0. McBride against George W. Venable and another.

Argued before DALY, 0. J., and PRYOR and GIEGERIOH, JJ.

A. B. Bright, for appellant. H. B. Gayley, for respondents.

No opinion. Order affirmed, with costs.
